name: Houston
summary: Hurricane Beryl has made landfall in Houston as a Category 1 storm, bringing powerful winds and heavy rainfall that have resulted in three deaths. The storm forced the cancellation of LAFC's match against Houston, which has been rescheduled for a later date. The storm has also caused widespread power outages in the Houston area, prompting officials to raise concerns about increased risks. In addition to the human toll, Beryl has also impacted the city's transportation, causing hundreds of flights to be canceled. While the full extent of the damage is still being assessed, Houstonians are celebrating the victories of Argentina and Ecuador in the Copa America.

name: Ap scores 2024
summary: AP scores, the results of college-level coursework taken by high school students, will be released on July 8th. Students can access their scores online through the College Board website. In a tragic incident, a stampede during a religious event in India has claimed the lives of at least 116 people and injured 80 more. In sports news, Turkey's Demiral scored twice to secure a 2-1 victory over Austria in soccer, advancing them to the Euro 2024 quarterfinals against the Netherlands. In basketball, Brionna Jones led the Connecticut Sun to an 83-72 win over the short-staffed Phoenix Mercury. The Las Vegas Aces set a WNBA record with the fifth-largest crowd ever, as A'ja Wilson scored 34 points in their victory over the Indiana Fever. The Cleveland Guardians' Steven Kwan became the major league baseball leader in batting average, reaching .367.

name: Texas
summary: Tropical Storm Beryl, which originated in the Gulf of Mexico, made landfall on the Texas coast and has been impacting the state since Monday. The storm, which is expected to become a hurricane, has already caused significant damage and power outages, with at least two fatalities reported. Acting Governor Dan Patrick has added 81 Texas counties to a disaster declaration, and officials are closely monitoring its path and potential impact on Houston. The storm system brought heavy rain and strong winds as it moved across the state, leaving millions without power. Although the storm's exact impact on the Texas coast and Houston is still uncertain, preparations and response efforts are underway, including a press conference by Acting Governor Dan Patrick. Additionally, Texas is experiencing a rise in COVID-19 cases as temperatures soar.

name: French elections
summary: In the recently concluded French elections of 2024, voters have overwhelmingly rejected the far-right by casting the highest number of votes for left-wing candidates. Consequently, no single political party has secured a majority in parliament, resulting in a hung parliament. This has created a political deadlock and left many wondering about the next steps and potential coalitions. The party led by Emmanuel Macron came in second, followed by Marine Le Pen's far-right party. Several news outlets have reported on this significant election and discussed the possible implications for France's political landscape. As analysts and politicians navigate the complex post-election scenario, negotiations and discussions are expected to determine the path forward for the country's governance.

name: Khyree Jackson
summary: Tragedy struck the football community as Minnesota Vikings rookie cornerback Khyree Jackson, along with two former high school teammates, lost their lives in a Maryland car accident. The incident occurred in Westminster, where Jackson's Dodge Charger was involved in a horrific crash, as confirmed by TMZ with first-hand photos. The news sent shockwaves through the Vikings organization, who released a statement expressing their condolences.
